{
  "doc_id": "17226",
  "text": "Vaccine preparation. Globo-H, Lewis Y, Tn(c), STn(c), and TF(c) were synthesized in the laboratory of Bio-Organic Chemistry at the Sloan-Kettering Institute as described previously (18, 20 -25) . MUC1-32mer(-CHGVTSAPDTRPAPGSTAPPAHGVTSAPDTRPA) was synthesized in an automated peptide synthesizer in the Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center Core Peptide Synthesis Facility, and the Tn-MUC1-32 GalNAc-glycopeptide with 8 mol GalNac incorporated was produced by in vitro glycosylation (see Fig. 1 ) with recombinant human polypeptide GalNAc-transferases T2 and T4 as described previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . GM2 was extracted from rabbit brains as GM1, treated with h-galactosidase to yield GM2, and provided by Progenics, Inc. [CITATION_3] .",
